CatDescriptText: Miss Joyce Blanding, 638 Chauncey Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 9, 1957, pg. 2 with question: "Do you believe that licensed taverns are as harmful to a neighborhood as speakeasies and gambling joints? Why?" answer reads: "No, I don't think so, because the taverns are under the law, and the others are not.  Mostly juveniles and kids under age, go there, whereas licensed taverns ask you for identification if they think that you are under age."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Joyce Blanding, wearing coat with flecked pattern and light colored blouse with bow at neck, holding paper bag, standing in front of brick wall and padlocked door
